                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.769,
                                "byte_start": 79990,
                                "byte_stop": 115099,
                                "text": "The judgments and opinion of the Court in 76-616, New York against Cathedral Academy will be announced by Mr. Justice Stewart."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.769,
                        "stop": 147.948,
                        "byte_start": 115099,
                        "byte_stop": 671820,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15043,
                            "name": "Potter Stewart",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/potter_stewart",
                            "last_name": "Stewart",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2687,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -353962800,
                                    "date_end": 362984400,
                                    "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2687"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32752,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56350,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/potter_stewart.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8298,
                            "identifier": "potter_stewart"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.769,
                                "stop": 15.712,
                                "byte_start": 115099,
                                "byte_stop": 142893,
                                "text": "This case is here by way of a direct appeal from the Court of Appeals of New York."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.712,
                                "stop": 40.021,
                                "byte_start": 142893,
                                "byte_stop": 240173,
                                "text": "In April of 1972, a three-judge United States District Court for the Southern District of New York, declared unconstitutional New York\u0027s Mandated Services Act, which authorized fixed payments to nonpublic schools as reimbursement for the cost of certain record keeping and testing services required by state law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.021,
                                "stop": 53.901,
                                "byte_start": 240173,
                                "byte_stop": 295657,
                                "text": "The court\u0027s order permanently enjoined any payments under the Act, including reimbursement for expenses that schools had already incurred in the last half of the 1971-1972 school year."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.901,
                                "stop": 63.023,
                                "byte_start": 295657,
                                "byte_stop": 332124,
                                "text": "This Court subsequently affirmed that judgment in a decision reported in Volume 413 of the United States reports."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.023,
                                "stop": 100.777,
                                "byte_start": 332124,
                                "byte_stop": 483112,
                                "text": "Two months after the District Court\u0027s decision, the New York State Legislature responded to it by enacting a law, that and I am quoting, \u0022recognized a moral obligation to provide a remedy whereby schools may recover the complete amount of expenses incurred by them prior to June of 1972, in reliance on\u0022 the invalidated mandated services Act, and which conferred jurisdiction on the New York Court of Claims \u0022to hear, audit and determine\u0022 the claims of nonprofit private schools for such expenses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.777,
                                "stop": 118.582,
                                "byte_start": 483112,
                                "byte_stop": 554374,
                                "text": "Thus the Act explicitly authorized what the District Court\u0027s injunction had explicitly prohibited, reimbursement to sectarian schools for their expenses of performing state-mandated services through the 1971-1972 academic year."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.582,
                                "stop": 126.325,
                                "byte_start": 554374,
                                "byte_stop": 585303,
                                "text": "The New York Court of Appeals upheld the validity of this new law, and its judgment is before us in the present case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.325,
                                "stop": 138.072,
                                "byte_start": 585303,
                                "byte_stop": 632323,
                                "text": "For the reasons stated and in an opinion file with the clerk today, we hold that the New York law is constitutionally invalid and accordingly we reverse the judgment of the New York Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.072,
                                "stop": 147.948,
                                "byte_start": 632323,
                                "byte_stop": 671820,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice and Mr. Justice Rehnquist have filed a dissenting statement and Mr. Justice White who also dissents has filed a separate dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
